
[1]divers

   DIVERS, a. S as z. [L., to turn.]

   1. Different; various.

   Thou shalt not sow thy fields with divers seeds. Deuteronomy 21.

   Nor let thy cattle gender with divers kinds. Leviticus 19.

   [This is now generally written diverse.]

   2. Several; sundry; more than one, but not a great number. We have
   divers examples of this kind. [This word is not obsolete even in common
   discourse, and is much used in law proceedings.]
